{"parentUuid":"7cd9cb9e-44ea-4a35-a8f5-1f27c623a313","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_011KarnM5hg26mvE4MfQXAi5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0144CBd6eFcj4raU7hmvfr9r","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Why materialized vs relay for other refs","subagent_type":"Explore","prompt":"I'm in /Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync. I need to understand a specific technical question:\n\nWhen git-sync handles \"other\" refs (refs/notes/*, refs/pull/*, custom namespaces) under `--all-refs`, it falls back from incremental relay to the materialized strategy. I want to understand **what materialized actually does differently** that makes it necessary for these refs.\n\nMy current understanding of relay (incremental):\n- It does a thin fetch from source using target's current ref tips as \"haves\"\n- Source sends a small pack of just the missing objects\n- Relay forwards that pack + ref-update commands to target\n- Target's receive-pack ingests it\n\nMy current understanding of materialized:\n- Something heavier — probably full clone or full object closure\n- But I don't know the specifics\n\nI want to know:\n\n1. **In `internal/strategy/materialized/materialized.go`**: what's the actual workflow? Does it fetch all objects, build a packfile from scratch, write a working repo? Quote the high-level entry point and the main steps.\n\n2. **In `internal/strategy/incremental/incremental.go`**: same — what's the actual workflow? Quote the high-level entry point.\n\n3. The key question: **why can't relay handle \"other\" refs?** Is it because:\n   - (a) relay's negotiation requires FF semantics to pick valid \"haves\"\n   - (b) relay assumes a specific ref-shape mapping that other refs break\n   - (c) something about the pack-building / fetch protocol that needs full closure\n   - (d) something else entirely\n\n   Look for comments or code that explain the actual technical limitation. The previous question I asked got an answer about \"FF safety as a contract\" — that's the *policy* reason. I want the *mechanism* reason. What concretely fails or becomes unsound if you try to relay a refs/notes/commits update?\n\n4. Is there anything about pack negotiation, thin packs, or object reachability that specifically requires materialized for these refs?\n\nReport file paths with line numbers, quote relevant blocks. Under 600 words. Focus on the mechanism, not the policy."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1477,"cache_read_input_tokens":45689,"output_tokens":813,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1477,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":813,"cache_read_input_tokens":45689,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1477,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1477},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CbAQqw5g8KjcTKu1MB5WQ","type":"assistant","uuid":"4da58b85-a220-4c2f-8438-50588da91ae9","timestamp":"2026-05-18T17:15:49.466Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync","sessionId":"c6533991-5707-4094-a756-614132c9eb65","version":"2.1.143","gitBranch":"main"}
