" the temp-file approach is correct. If (1) shows \"idle timeout during upload,\" the right fix is probably **send keepalive frames in sideband-during-progress** or **chunked-but-with-server-aware framing**, not buffer-then-send.\n\n**My recommendation**\n\nDon't implement step 1 yet. **Confirm the diagnosis first** — capture the actual failure mode (server log line, response code, or tcpdump showing where the connection dies). Twenty minutes of confirming the cause saves a fix that masks the wrong symptom.\n\nIf the diagnosis holds up:\n- Implementing the temp-file spool is the right narrow fix\n- I'd also set `req.ContentLength` explicitly and let Go pick a non-chunked transfer\n- Add a code comment naming the backend bug being worked around, so this doesn't become mystery code when someone revisits in six months\n- Skip the \"if conn is `*HTTPConn`\" type-switch in `PushObjects`. That leaks transport knowledge upward. Push the buffering decision into the transport: `HTTPConn.PostRPCStreamBody` can spool internally when ContentLength is unknown. SSH stays untouched. Cleaner layering.\n\nWant me to dig into the actual failure mode (run a materialized push against the target, capture the request/response)?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1923,"cache_read_input_tokens":64164,"output_tokens":4181,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1923,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":4181,"cache_read_input_tokens":64164,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1923,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1923},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CbAWzGvwYxa4NDLUSysah","type":"assistant","uuid":"d487e1ae-e55b-4379-abd3-6c40bb0658e3","timestamp":"2026-05-18T18:3