{"parentUuid":"1b61ef76-f27c-42f3-9d3a-f071cdf6707a","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01UddbY8fV9pxwkm896btuUd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"That's a clean framing. \"New connection per step\" lines up with what git-sync actually does over HTTP:\n\n| Step | Request |\n|---|---|\n| Discover source refs | `GET source/info/refs` |\n| Fetch | `POST source/upload-pack` |\n| Discover target refs | `GET target/info/refs` |\n| Push | `POST target/receive-pack` |\n\nEach step is one HTTP request. There's no tight back-to-back request pattern where pooling actually buys us anything. And between steps there's real work (planning, local materialization, closure walking). So \"fresh connection per request\" matches the actual workflow rather than fighting it.\n\n**Library angle**\n\nThis is solvable cleanly with the API already there:\n\n- `NewHTTPTransport` returns the default git-sync-tuned transport — keep-alives off, \"new connection per step\" semantics\n- `NewHTTPConn(ep, label, auth, rt http.RoundTripper)` accepts any RoundTripper, so library users who *want* pooling (e.g., embedding git-sync in a long-running server that does many syncs against the same host) can pass their own transport with whatever pool config they want\n\nThat way:\n- CLI gets the safe default for free\n- Library users get the same default\n- Library users with a different workflow can opt out by passing their own transport\n\n**One thing worth fixing while we're here**\n\nThe current `NewHTTPTransport(false)` returns `http.DefaultTransport` — the package-level shared one. That means our settings would leak into any other code in the same process using `http.DefaultTransport`. For a library that's a latent footgun. Whatever we change, we should also switch to always returning a `Clone()` so our config is isolated.\n\n**Proposed concrete change**\n\n```go\nfunc NewHTTPTransport(skipTLS bool) http.RoundTripper {\n    base, ok := http.DefaultTransport.(*http.Transport)\n    if !ok {\n        return http.DefaultTransport\n    }\n    tc := base.Clone()\n\n    // git-sync's HTTP workflow is coarse-grained: info-refs, then\n    // upload-pack or receive-pack. Between them there's planning,\n    // a source fetch, and local object materialization — gaps long\n    // enough that CDN edges close idle TLS sockets, surfacing as\n    // \"use of closed network connection\" on the next POST. Pool\n    // reuse would save at most one handshake per sync, so we\n    // prefer a fresh connection per request and avoid the race.\n    // Library callers wanting pooling can pass their own\n    // RoundTripper to NewHTTPConn.\n    tc.DisableKeepAlives = true\n\n    if skipTLS {\n        if tc.TLSClientConfig == nil {\n            tc.TLSClientConfig = &tls.Config{MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12}\n        }\n        tc.TLSClientConfig.InsecureSkipVerify = true\n    }\n    return tc\n}\n```\n\nTwo behavior changes from current code: (1) always clone, never return shared default; (2) keep-alives off.\n\nWant me to apply it?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2091,"cache_read_input_tokens":113451,"output_tokens":4249,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2091,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":6,"output_tokens":4249,"cache_read_input_tokens":113451,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2091,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2091},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CbC55JTaybK1kVdqzZHMK","type":"assistant","uuid":"67582a97-8154-4331-81ae-698432f29125","timestamp":"2026-05-19T14:18:30.785Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync","sessionId":"c6533991-5707-4094-a7